k. Wide-ranging and accessible, these interviews provide a fascinating guide to the ideas, concerns, and personalities of thinkers who have shaped modern intellectual life. This book will be an essential point of entry for students, teachers, scholars, and anyone seeking to understand contemporary culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311070729840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082329135940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823291359423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823291359/original  a978-3-11-070729-8  Fordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK